Asteroids contain hidden messages in their magnetic fields that could provide clues about the death of our planet.

This is according to British scientists who have, for the first time, captured the dying moments a meteorite's magnetic field - a fate that could be shared with Earth.

They unravelled the message by looking at tiny 'space magnets' in meteorites which retain a memory of the birth and death of the asteroid's core.

