However, the Earth's core is freezing rather slowly.

The solid inner core is getting bigger, and eventually the liquid outer core will disappear, killing the Earth's magnetic field, which protects us from the sun's radiation.

'There's no need to panic just yet, however,' said Professor Harrison. 'The core won't completely freeze for billions of years, and chances are, the sun will get us first.'

